TITLE: Defining Traits in Koota
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to define traits, which are the building blocks of state in Koota. Examples include basic traits with default values, traits with callbacks for initial values, and tag traits with no data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/pmndrs/koota/blob/main/packages/publish/README.md#2025-04-12_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
import { trait } from 'koota';

// Basic trait with default values
const Position = trait({ x: 0, y: 0 });
const Velocity = trait({ x: 0, y: 0 });

// Trait with a callback for initial value
// âš ï¸ Must be an object
const Mesh = trait(() => new THREE.Mesh());

// Tag trait (no data)
const IsActive = trait();
```

