TITLE: Using Query Modifiers in Koota
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the use of various query modifiers in Koota, including Not, Or, Added, Removed, and Changed modifiers.
SOURCE: https://github.com/pmndrs/koota/blob/main/README.md#2025-04-12_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { Not, Or, createAdded, createRemoved, createChanged } from 'koota';

const staticEntities = world.query(Position, Not(Velocity));

const movingOrVisible = world.query(Or(Velocity, Renderable));

const Added = createAdded();
const newPositions = world.query(Added(Position));

const Removed = createRemoved();
const stoppedEntities = world.query(Removed(Velocity));

const Changed = createChanged();
const movedEntities = world.query(Changed(Position));
```

